welcome the general theme of our research is the study of human brain from clinical and system neuroscience perspective using the tools of functional imaging fmri intracranial electrocorticography ecog and electrical brain stimulation ebs the main impetus for our research is to understand the anatomical and physiological signatures of behavioral expression and cognitive experience in humans and how these might be broken in patients with epilepsy using our sophisticated research tools our goal is to help patients with uncontrolled epilepsy to gain seizure freedom without cognitive deficits
